# Design doc governance

## Source of truth

| Layer | Location | Who edits | Agent default |
|-------|----------|-----------|---------------|
| **Gameplay index** | `docs/design/Overview.md` | **User only** | Read-only |
| **Gameplay systems** | `docs/design/systems/*.md` | **User only** | Read-only |
| **Edit rules** | `docs/design/DESIGN_DOC_GOVERNANCE.md` | User | Read-only unless user asks |
| **AI / process docs** | `docs/ai/` | User + agent per workflow | Editable per workflow |
| **Implementation specs** | `docs/ai/Core/`, etc. | User + agent when tasked | Editable when implementing |

`docs/design/` is **not** under `docs/ai/`.

## Agent may read gameplay docs when

- Bootstrap: start from `Overview.md`, then task-relevant `systems/*.md`.
- User asks about rules or scopes implementation (cite section).

## Agent must NOT (default)

- Edit `Overview.md` or `systems/*.md` without **explicit user request** (file + scope).
- Treat chat as approved design changes.

## When user explicitly delegates

Phrases like: 「帮我在 effects.md 里改…」「更新 equipment 章节…」

1. Confirm path under `docs/design/systems/`.
2. Minimal edit only.
3. Note in `docs/ai/PROGRESS_LOG.md`.

